  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Junea. ?] I said, yes, her name is the same.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She was in your place?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You are here, now where is she?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, you'll have a very hard battle, not easy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But if you go back to Germany and stay in [NON-ENGLISH], work-- it was an ambulance, not a big hospital, had set up for all survivors there in a little [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Furth was a small city, but that was a part of the city that it-- it was given to us to live there.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were beautiful homes with gardens, a small enclosure for about, say, 800 people, 1,000 people, small houses, and we had to share.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was not a big hospital, a small one set up quickly, with a ambulance, that people-- a few rooms like a hospital.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's where I worked there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And not, it was not far from [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That woman said, if you want to know more about your daughter, where she is, because I can't tell you much.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I know she was alive and she was in my place.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "From my place, it took her-- she was very sickly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She seemed very thin after the war, not eating.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The whole story, you'll hear when you go back where, where you work, I told her, go back there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had to go back from there, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] back to Germany from border, Polish, Czechoslovakian and wait until-- inquire and go to [?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Menachem, ?] to the headquarters of the Jewish community, these people who helped me to get back to my name.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a-- there is a woman from Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She is a rabbi's wife-- the rabbi was killed-- an elderly woman-- she's alive-- and her son.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
